18 SECTION 8. A new section to chapter 54-23.3 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
19 and enacted as follows:
20 Native American re-entry program - Report to legislative management.
21 1. The department of corrections and rehabilitation, in cooperation with representatives
22 from each federally recognized American Indian tribe in the state, and the Indian
23 affairs commission, shall establish and administer a re-entry program to provide
24 re - entry services and support tailored to the needs of Native Americans .
25 2. The Native American re-entry program shall:
26 a. Assess the needs of Native American adult offenders with the goal of reducing
27 recidivism;
28 b. Identify culturally responsive training opportunities and provide training to
29 department staff;
30 c. Designate a Native American liaison to operate within the department regarding
31 parole and probation services for adult offenders; and
Page No. 4 25.0182.05000

