1 d. Develop oversight and evaluation processes, including outcome-based metrics
2 related to recidivism reduction.
3 3. The department of correction and rehabilitation shall provide an annual report to the
4 legislative management regarding the status of the Native American re-entry program.
5 SECTION 9. MISSOURI RIVER CORRECTIONAL CENTER PLANNING AND DESIGN -
6 STEERING COMMITTEE - REPORT. The appropriation in the adult services line item in
7 section 1 of this Act includes $20,000,000 from the strategic investment and improvements fund
8 for planning and design for a new minimum security male correctional facility for the Missouri
9 River correctional center. The department of corrections and rehabilitation shall establish a
10 Missouri River correctional center steering committee to oversee the design and construction of
11 the new Missouri River correctional center facility, including other options, for the biennium
12 beginning July 1, 2025, and ending June 30, 2027. The committee must include one member of
13 the senate appointed by the senate majority leader, one member of the house appointed by the
14 house majority leader, and one member of the minority party from either the senate or the
15 house appointed by the minority leaders of the senate and the house. The department of
16 corrections and rehabilitation shall provide a quarterly report to the legislative management
17 regarding the planning and design of a new minimum security facility.
18 SECTION 10. LEGISLATIVE MANAGEMENT STUDY - SENTENCING, CORRECTIONS,
19 AND PAROLE OVERSIGHT. During the 2025-26 interim, the legislative management shall
20 study the sentencing, correctional, and parole systems within the state, with a focus on
21 improving transparency, consistency, and outcomes in the administration of justice. The study
22 must include a comprehensive review of:
23 1. Sentencing requirements and incarceration impacts, including an evaluation of the
24 potential impacts of requiring offenders sentenced to the custody of the department of
25 corrections and rehabilitation to serve eighty-five percent of their terms in secured
26 facilities. The study must include:
27 a. Cost analyses;
28 b. Consideration of recidivism trends;
29 c. Consideration of rehabilitation and re-entry opportunities; and
30 d. Input from:
31 (1) District court judges regarding sentencing decisions;
Page No. 5 25.0182.05000

