1 (2) State's attorney and defense attorneys regarding charging practices, plea
2 negotiations, and trial resources;
3 (3) The department of corrections and rehabilitation regarding inmate
4 classification, housing, placement authority, and transitional services
5 including work or educational release; and
6 (4) The parole board regarding parole eligibility and release decisions.
7 2. The structure and function of the parole board, including chapter 12-59 and any rules
8 adopted by the parole board. The study must include:
9 a. Membership structure, appointment process, terms, quorum, and meeting
10 transparency;
11 b. Parole eligibility requirements and determinations;
12 c. Victim rights and notification systems; and
13 d. The role and input of the department of corrections and rehabilitation in
14 parole-related matters.
15 The legislative management shall report its findings and recommendations, together with any
16 legislation required to implement the recommendations, to the seventieth legislative assembly.
